      "writtenOn": "2018-04-18T22:28:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hey, i heard to like avoiding allocs. Here is an idea:\n\nswap all shall invocations to the end of slice:\n\nr :\u003d len(invs) - 1\nfor l, inv :\u003d range invs{\n  if l \u003e\u003d r{ break }\n  if inv.Status \u003d\u003d \"\" {invs[r] \u003d inv; r-- }\n}\n...\n... datastore.Get(c, invs[r:])...",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 455,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 455,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "9d146de55fde090f948129b2651d3cb01dedeec6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3881dcfc_2ce7289a",
        "filename": "scheduler/appengine/engine/invquery.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 455,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-18T22:40:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems like an overkill to me :)\n\nO(|invs|) ~\u003d PageSize (that can be up to 500) \nO(|shallow|) ~\u003d number of active + recently finished invocations (which is expected to be ~10).\n\nI felt bad allocating PageSize slices, but allocating smaller ones is fine, I think.",
      "parentUuid": "01ab0c90_ceee18a8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 455,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 455,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "9d146de55fde090f948129b2651d3cb01dedeec6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "178524c0_b506ebba",
        "filename": "scheduler/appengine/engine/invquery.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 455,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-18T22:44:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "not that I insist on adopting my optimization, but why is allocating 500 pointers worse than 10 pointers?",
      "parentUuid": "3881dcfc_2ce7289a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 455,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 455,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "9d146de55fde090f948129b2651d3cb01dedeec6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "73ffc8f5_645c85ea",
        "filename": "scheduler/appengine/engine/invquery.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 455,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-18T22:48:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Because allocating 500 pointers is 50x more memory in a memory constraint environment? :)",
      "parentUuid": "178524c0_b506ebba",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 455,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 455,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "9d146de55fde090f948129b2651d3cb01dedeec6",
